James Roosevelt I (July 16, 1828 – December 8, 1900), known as "Squire James",[1] was an American businessman and horse breeder, and the father of American President Franklin Delano Roosevelt.



Contents


1 Early life
2 Career
3 Personal life
4 In popular culture
5 Legacy
6 See also
